Emacs comes with an AdvancedDeskCalculator called `calc'.
Try it! `M-x calc'.

AndrewHyatt wrote a number of tutorials on Google+:

* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/YG2vYpGoLn3 Solving Equations] -- basic algebra
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/RYiWfs9NMTS Display] -- show square roots and superscripts using ASCII art
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/bNw8CqAKpBR Fractions]
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/VzAQ8QLyCXj Strings and Binary]
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/ggiQGdLyX41 Pi and Precision]
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/LNi5SJxXXxC Units]
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/QuN7vdJpSZN Random Numbers]
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/YFKHGksdeWy Time] -- seconds since the Epoch
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/TWdjoj1zirv Digit Grouping] -- 1,910,255,938.01 and the like
* [https://plus.google.com/101505495157778834572/posts/goYiW8VfamS Hex Numbers]
